module

public import TauCeti.AlgebraicGeometry.WeilDivisor.DegreeSplitting

/-!
# The image of the degree map and the degree quotient `Cl(X)/Pic‚Āį`

This file computes the image of the (weighted) degree homomorphism and identifies the quotient
of the divisor class group by the abstract `Pic‚Āį`, continuing the Jacobian roadmap's Layer A.

`TauCeti.AlgebraicGeometry.WeilDivisor.Principal` builds, for an `OrderSystem S` whose principal
divisors have weighted degree zero, the descended weighted degree `weightedDegreeClass` on the
class group `Cl(X)` and its kernel `picZero`, the abstract `Pic‚Āį`.
`TauCeti.AlgebraicGeometry.WeilDivisor.DegreeSplitting` then shows that a weight-one base point
makes the descended degree *surjective* and splits `Cl(X) ‚ČÉ+ picZero √ó ‚Ą§`. That file's docstring
flags the general case, where there is no weight-one point: "the image of the weighted degree map
is `d¬∑‚Ą§` for the index `d` of the residue degrees". This file supplies exactly that general
picture.

The image of the weighted degree is computed unconditionally, before any principal-divisor
hypothesis: since the point divisors generate the free abelian group of Weil divisors and
`weightedDegree w (ofPoint x) = w x`, the image is the subgroup of `‚Ą§` generated by the weights,

`(weightedDegree w).range = AddSubgroup.closure (Set.range w)`.

Every subgroup of `‚Ą§` is `d¬∑‚Ą§` for a unique `d ‚Č• 0`, so this is the promised index `d`. When
principal divisors have weighted degree zero the same computation descends to the class group,
`(weightedDegreeClass w h).range = AddSubgroup.closure (Set.range w)`, and Noether's first
isomorphism theorem then identifies the *degree quotient*

`Cl(X) ‚ßł Pic‚Āį ‚ČÉ+ (weightedDegreeClass w h).range`,

the degree quotient of the class group (the divisor-class analogue of `Pic/Pic‚Āį`; no Picard
scheme or N√©ron‚ÄďSeveri construction is built here). When the weights generate all of `‚Ą§` ‚ÄĒ for
instance from a weight-one base point ‚ÄĒ this image is `‚ä§`, recovering `Cl(X) ‚ßł Pic‚Āį ‚ČÉ+ ‚Ą§` and
reconciling with the splitting of `DegreeSplitting`. In the unweighted setting the degree map is
already surjective on a nonempty point type.

This advances `TauCetiRoadmap/JacobianChallenge/README.md`, Layer A, "Degree" and "`Pic‚Āį X =
ker deg` (as an abstract group)", by computing the image of the degree map and identifying the
degree quotient of the class group with it. It reuses Tau Ceti's `WeilDivisor`, `OrderSystem`,
and `DegreeSplitting` API together with Mathlib's `AddSubgroup.closure` and first-isomorphism
(`QuotientAddGroup.quotientKerEquivRange` / `quotientKerEquivOfRightInverse`) machinery; no
external mathematics is vendored.
-/

public section

namespace TauCeti

namespace AlgebraicGeometry

namespace WeilDivisor

variable {X : Type*}

/-! ### The image of the weighted degree on Weil divisors -/

/-- The image of the weighted degree homomorphism is the subgroup of `‚Ą§` generated by the
weights. The point divisors generate the free abelian group of Weil divisors and
`weightedDegree w (ofPoint x) = w x`, so the image is `AddSubgroup.closure (Set.range w)`; being
a subgroup of `‚Ą§`, it is `d¬∑‚Ą§` for a unique `d ‚Č• 0`, the index of the weights. -/
lemma weightedDegree_range (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§) :
    (weightedDegree w : WeilDivisor X ‚Üí+ ‚Ą§).range = AddSubgroup.closure (Set.range w) := by
  apply le_antisymm
  ¬∑ rintro _ ‚ü®D, rfl‚ü©
    rw [weightedDegree_apply, Finsupp.sum]
    refine sum_mem fun x _ => ?_
    exact AddSubgroup.zsmul_mem _ (AddSubgroup.subset_closure (Set.mem_range_self x)) (D x)
  ¬∑ rw [AddSubgroup.closure_le]
    rintro _ ‚ü®x, rfl‚ü©
    exact ‚ü®ofPoint x, weightedDegree_ofPoint w x‚ü©

/-- On a nonempty point type the unweighted degree map is surjective: a single point has degree
`1`, so its integer multiples realise every degree. -/
lemma degree_surjective [Nonempty X] : Function.Surjective (degree : WeilDivisor X ‚Üí+ ‚Ą§) := by
  intro n
  obtain ‚ü®x‚ü© := ‚ÄĻNonempty X‚Äļ
  exact ‚ü®n ‚ÄĘ ofPoint x, by simp [map_zsmul, degree_ofPoint]‚ü©

/-- On a nonempty point type the unweighted degree map hits all of `‚Ą§`. -/
lemma degree_range_eq_top [Nonempty X] : (degree : WeilDivisor X ‚Üí+ ‚Ą§).range = ‚ä§ :=
  AddMonoidHom.range_eq_top.mpr degree_surjective

variable {G : Type*} [AddCommGroup G] (S : OrderSystem X G)

namespace OrderSystem

/-! ### The image of the degree on the class group -/

/-- The image of the descended weighted degree on the class group is the same subgroup of `‚Ą§`
generated by the weights. The class map `divisorClass` is surjective, so it does not change the
image of the degree; the value is `weightedDegree_range` transported through the quotient. -/
lemma weightedDegreeClass_range (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w) :
    (weightedDegreeClass w h).range = AddSubgroup.closure (Set.range w) := by
  rw [‚Üź weightedDegree_range w]
  apply le_antisymm
  ¬∑ rintro _ ‚ü®c, rfl‚ü©
    obtain ‚ü®D, rfl‚ü© := S.divisorClass_surjective c
    exact ‚ü®D, (weightedDegreeClass_divisorClass w h D).symm‚ü©
  ¬∑ rintro _ ‚ü®D, rfl‚ü©
    exact ‚ü®S.divisorClass D, weightedDegreeClass_divisorClass w h D‚ü©

/-- The descended weighted degree hits all of `‚Ą§` exactly when the weights generate `‚Ą§`, i.e.
`AddSubgroup.closure (Set.range w) = ‚ä§`. This is the general surjectivity criterion; a weight-one
base point is the special case `weightedDegreeClass_range_eq_top_of_weight_one`, but weights such
as `2` and `3` already generate `‚Ą§` with no weight-one point. -/
lemma weightedDegreeClass_range_eq_top (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w)
    (hw : AddSubgroup.closure (Set.range w) = ‚ä§) : (weightedDegreeClass w h).range = ‚ä§ := by
  rw [weightedDegreeClass_range, hw]

/-- With a weight-one base point the descended weighted degree hits all of `‚Ą§`; this is the
`AddSubgroup`-level restatement of `weightedDegreeClass_surjective`, a special case of
`weightedDegreeClass_range_eq_top`. -/
lemma weightedDegreeClass_range_eq_top_of_weight_one (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w)
    {x‚āÄ : X} (hx‚āÄ : w x‚āÄ = 1) : (weightedDegreeClass w h).range = ‚ä§ :=
  AddMonoidHom.range_eq_top.mpr (S.weightedDegreeClass_surjective w h hx‚āÄ)

/-! ### The degree quotient `Cl(X)/Pic‚Āį` -/

/-- **The degree quotient.** The class group modulo the abstract `Pic‚Āį` is isomorphic to the image
of the degree, `Cl(X) ‚ßł Pic‚Āį ‚ČÉ+ (weightedDegreeClass w h).range`. This is Noether's first
isomorphism theorem for the descended weighted degree, whose kernel is `picZero` by definition;
the image is `AddSubgroup.closure (Set.range w)` by `weightedDegreeClass_range`. It is the degree
quotient of the class group, the divisor-class analogue of `Pic/Pic‚Āį`; no Picard scheme is
constructed here. -/
@[expose] noncomputable def classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivDegreeRange (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§)
    (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w) :
    S.ClassGroup ‚ßł picZero w h ‚ČÉ+ (weightedDegreeClass w h).range :=
  QuotientAddGroup.quotientKerEquivRange (weightedDegreeClass w h)

@[simp]
lemma coe_classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivDegreeRange_mk (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w)
    (c : S.ClassGroup) :
    (S.classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivDegreeRange w h (QuotientAddGroup.mk c) : ‚Ą§) =
      weightedDegreeClass w h c :=
  rfl

@[simp]
lemma classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivDegreeRange_symm_apply (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§)
    (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w) (c : S.ClassGroup) :
    (S.classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivDegreeRange w h).symm
        ‚ü®weightedDegreeClass w h c, c, rfl‚ü© = QuotientAddGroup.mk c := by
  rw [AddEquiv.symm_apply_eq]
  exact Subtype.ext (S.coe_classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivDegreeRange_mk w h c).symm

/-- **The degree quotient at a surjective degree.** When the descended weighted degree is
surjective ‚ÄĒ equivalently when the weights generate `‚Ą§`, see `weightedDegreeClass_range_eq_top` ‚ÄĒ
the class group modulo the abstract `Pic‚Āį` is `‚Ą§`, `Cl(X) ‚ßł Pic‚Āį ‚ČÉ+ ‚Ą§`. A weight-one base point
is the special case `classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivIntOfWeightOne`. -/
@[expose] noncomputable def classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivInt (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§)
    (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w)
    (hsurj : Function.Surjective (weightedDegreeClass w h)) : S.ClassGroup ‚ßł picZero w h ‚ČÉ+ ‚Ą§ :=
  QuotientAddGroup.quotientKerEquivOfSurjective (weightedDegreeClass w h) hsurj

@[simp]
lemma classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivInt_mk (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w)
    (hsurj : Function.Surjective (weightedDegreeClass w h)) (c : S.ClassGroup) :
    S.classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivInt w h hsurj (QuotientAddGroup.mk c) =
      weightedDegreeClass w h c :=
  rfl

/-- The inverse of `classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivInt` sends `weightedDegreeClass w h c` back to
the class `[c]`. Since `weightedDegreeClass w h` is surjective this characterises the inverse on
all of `‚Ą§`, so downstream code need not unfold the choice-based right inverse. -/
@[simp]
lemma classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivInt_symm_weightedDegreeClass (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§)
    (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w)
    (hsurj : Function.Surjective (weightedDegreeClass w h)) (c : S.ClassGroup) :
    (S.classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivInt w h hsurj).symm (weightedDegreeClass w h c) =
      QuotientAddGroup.mk c := by
  rw [AddEquiv.symm_apply_eq, classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivInt_mk]

/-- **The degree quotient at a rational point.** With a weight-one base point the degree section
`n ‚Ü¶ n ‚ÄĘ [x‚āÄ]` is a genuine right inverse of the descended weighted degree, so the class group
modulo the abstract `Pic‚Āį` is `‚Ą§`, `Cl(X) ‚ßł Pic‚Āį ‚ČÉ+ ‚Ą§`, with an explicit inverse. Together with
`DegreeSplitting`'s `Cl(X) ‚ČÉ+ picZero √ó ‚Ą§` this exhibits the degree as the projection to the `‚Ą§`
factor. -/
@[expose] noncomputable def classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivIntOfWeightOne (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§)
    (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w) {x‚āÄ : X} (hx‚āÄ : w x‚āÄ = 1) :
    S.ClassGroup ‚ßł picZero w h ‚ČÉ+ ‚Ą§ :=
  QuotientAddGroup.quotientKerEquivOfRightInverse (weightedDegreeClass w h) (S.degreeSection x‚āÄ)
    fun n => S.weightedDegreeClass_degreeSection_of_weight_one w h hx‚āÄ n

@[simp]
lemma classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivIntOfWeightOne_mk (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§) (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w)
    {x‚āÄ : X} (hx‚āÄ : w x‚āÄ = 1) (c : S.ClassGroup) :
    S.classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivIntOfWeightOne w h hx‚āÄ (QuotientAddGroup.mk c) =
      weightedDegreeClass w h c :=
  rfl

@[simp]
lemma classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivIntOfWeightOne_symm_apply (w : X ‚Üí ‚Ą§)
    (h : S.IsWeightedDegreeZero w) {x‚āÄ : X} (hx‚āÄ : w x‚āÄ = 1) (n : ‚Ą§) :
    (S.classGroupQuotientPicZeroEquivIntOfWeightOne w h hx‚āÄ).symm n =
      QuotientAddGroup.mk (S.degreeSection x‚āÄ n) :=
  rfl

end OrderSystem

end WeilDivisor

end AlgebraicGeometry

